Smoking prevalence is still high in some countries (table 1
), especially in men (Figure 1, Figure 2
). South Asia has the highest use of smokeless tobacco worldwide (figure 3
). Most of the six million annual tobacco deaths worldwide are in Asia. In WHO's South-East Asia region, an estimated 1·3 million people die every year from tobacco-related disease,15 whereas in the Western Pacific region14 two people die every minute, placing a huge burden on health-care systems.
